>>a635b19e-510e-4a10-9656-ac473da85496
A tor relay has a setting that disconnects a peer if they have too many concurrent connections. Since zeronet doesn't allow you to change your number of connections, you instead isolate connections more, so you don't get banned from tor nodes because you're spreading your connections harder.
There's a donwnside do that, starting tor connections is slow, so if you're starting a tor connection for everything you do, then everything you do slows down.
You can isolate tor connections by destination IP for instance, that should make every zeronet peer you have use a different connection.
Read the manual.
